{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-all-timeline-js","path":"/2016/07/05/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"awesomeListRepo":"sindresorhus/awesome-electron","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rbSvc8_BHaw\">Building Desktop Apps with Node.js and Electron</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-05T19:08:40.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"dastergon/awesome-sre","categoryHTML":"<h2>Reliability</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://speakerdeck.com/garethr/the-two-sides-to-google-infrastructure-for-everyone-else\">The Two Sides to Google Infrastructure for Everyone Else</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-05T18:40:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jagracey/Awesome-Unicode","categoryHTML":"<h1>Quirks and Troubleshooting</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>String length is typically determined by counting codepoints.</strong> This means that surrogate pairs would count as two characters. Combining multiple diacritics may be stacked over the same character. <code>a + ̈  == ̈a   </code>, increasing length, while only producing a single character.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-05T18:04:07.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jagracey/Awesome-Unicode","categoryHTML":"<h1>Quirks and Troubleshooting</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>Similarily, reversing strings often is a non-trivial task.</strong> Again, surrogate pairs and diacritics must be reversed together. <a href=\"https://github.com/mathiasbynens/esrever\">ES Reverser</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mathiasbynens/esrever\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">859</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":859,\"repo\":\"mathiasbynens/esrever\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> provides a pretty good solution.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-05T18:04:07.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jagracey/Awesome-Unicode","categoryHTML":"<h1>Quirks and Troubleshooting</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><strong>Upper and lower case mappings are not always one-to-one.</strong> They can also be:\n<ul>\n<li>One-to-many: (ß → SS )</li>\n<li>Contextual: (…Σ ↔ …ς AND …ΣΤ… ↔ …στ… )</li>\n<li>Locale-sensitive: ( I ↔ ı AND İ ↔ i )</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-05T18:04:07.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jagracey/Awesome-Unicode","categoryHTML":"<h1>Unicode Versions</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode9.0.0/\">Version 9.0.0</a> (Latest Version, August 2016 - adds exactly 7,500 characters)</li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-05T17:58:45.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"jagracey/Awesome-Unicode","categoryHTML":"<h1>Unicode Versions</h1>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode8.0.0/\">Version 8.0.0</a></li>","updatedAt":"2016-07-05T17:58:45.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"thangchung/awesome-dotnet-core","categoryHTML":"<h2>Frameworks, Libraries and Tools</h2><h3>Security</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/aspnet/Security\">Security</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/aspnet/Security\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\"